PZ Cussons has denied a report that it is leaving Nigeria as a result of tough conditions. The company, in a statement, said the story was totally false and misleading and created the impression that PZ had decided to leave Nigeria. “The trading statement issued to the London Stock Exchange (LSE) was clear on our continued operations in Nigeria. While these conditions prevail, we will maintain our strong market shares in key product categories in Nigeria until growth returns to the market,”PZ said. PZ Cussons re-launches Venus PZ Cussons shareholders approve N1.9bn dividend Scores die in Army, Shi’ite clash in zaria